				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I think that the lack of interest on the MMC5 is due to the impossibility of producing new carts. The MMC5 is by far the most complex (NES) mapper there is, and so far nobody has successfully replicated it in hardware, which means that in order to make a cartridge of a homebrew that uses ExGrafix you have to destroy an original MMC5 cart.
<br />
<br />I don't think anybody wants to make software that can't be easily put into real carts, so that's why the MMC5 is largely ignored. Personally, I don't see much appeal in running NES software exclusively in emulators.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

