				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">C64 have a bitmap mode, although it is not very useful for action games. There is a text mode that used similar to NES as well.
<br />
<br />I'd better worry about other differences than the attributes size. For example, scrolling and number/sizes of sprites. NES is much superior in these features, and universal solutuion like a cross platform library should aim for lowest specs of all the supported platforms. 8 large sprites that C64 provide, being recreated on NES with its 8x8 sprites, would be pretty useless, at least because of the 8 sprites per line limitation. You would prefer to use native NES sprite features, but you can't recreate them on C64.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

